{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844577653,"sessionID":"ses_2876a4bc9ffeBrXPHdSEdVEE8O","part":{"id":"prt_d7895ce2b001UwZ8H7IfLZP4T7","messageID":"msg_d7895c2690011cxh1FvvOZnIRF","sessionID":"ses_2876a4bc9ffeBrXPHdSEdVEE8O","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a0302c9940964bde939ba83e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Core Types & Error Definitions\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Add `DeleteOptions` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: GracePeriodSeconds, Force, LabelSelector, Preconditions\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Add `ErrSandboxNotFound`, `ErrDeletionFailed`, `ErrStaleFinalizer`, `ErrOrphanedResource` to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Add `WebhookConfig` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: URL, Timeout, RetryCount\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Add `AuditLogEntry` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: SandboxID, Namespace, Reason, Initiator, Duration, ResourcesCleaned\n16: - [ ] **1.5** Add `DeletionEvent` struct to `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — fields: Type, Reason, Message, InvolvedObject, Timestamp\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Phase 2: Deletion Handlers (HTTP Layer)\n21: \n22: - [ ] **2.1** Implement `handleDeleteSandbox` in `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes/{sessionId}\n23: - [ ] **2.2** Add route registration for sandbox DELETE in server.go (existing agentruntime/codeinterpreter pattern)\n24: - [ ] **2.3** Implement query param binding for DeleteOptions (gracePeriodSeconds, force, labelSelector)\n25: - [ ] **2.4** Add HTTP 404 response for non-existent sandbox (AR-006-004)\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Phase 3: WorkloadManager Interface Extension\n30: \n31: - [ ] **3.1** Add `DeleteSandbox(ctx, namespace, sessionID string, opts DeleteOptions) error` to WorkloadManager interface\n32: - [ ] **3.2** Add `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, namespace, sessionID string) (*Sandbox, error)` to interface\n33: - [ ] **3.3** Add `ListSandboxes(ctx, namespace string, opts ListOptions) (*SandboxList, error)` to interface\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Phase 4: Graceful Shutdown Implementation\n38: \n39: - [ ] **4.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful.go` — implement `drainConnections(sandboxID)` to stop routing new traffic\n40: - [ ] **4.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful.go` — implement `waitForConnections(sandboxID, timeout)` with context\n41: - [ ] **4.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful.go` — implement `executePreDeleteHook(sandbox, hookConfig)` with timeout\n42: - [ ] **4.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful.go` — implement `sendSIGTERM(podName, namespace)` via exec\n43: - [ ] **4.5** Integrate graceful shutdown into DeleteSandbox flow with gracePeriodSeconds support (AR-006-010)\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## Phase 5: TTL & Expiration Logic\n48: \n49: - [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration.go` — implement `isExpiredByTTL(sandbox)` check\n50: - [ ] **5.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration.go` — implement `isExpiredByIdleTimeout(sandbox)` check\n51: - [ ] **5.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration.go` — implement `isExpiredByMaxLifetime(sandbox)` check\n52: - [ ] **5.4** Add DefaultTTL, DefaultIdleTimeout, DefaultMaxLifetime constants to `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n53: - [ ] **5.5** Implement expiration check in garbage collector loop (AR-006-020, AR-006-021, AR-006-022)\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Phase 6: Batch Deletion Operations\n58: \n59: - [ ] **6.1** Implement `handleDeleteAllSandboxes` — DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes?deleteAll=true\n60: - [ ] **6.2** Implement `handleDeleteByLabelSelector` — DELETE with labelSelector query param\n61: - [ ] **6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/batch.go` — implement `deleteStaleSandboxes()` for Unknown/Failed state > 1hr\n62: - [ ] **6.4** Add async deletion support for batch operations > 10 sandboxes\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## Phase 7: Resource Cleanup\n67: \n68: - [ ] **7.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go` — implement `cleanupServices(namespace, ownerRef)` using ownerReference\n69: - [ ] **7.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go` — implement `cleanupConfigMaps(namespace, ownerRef)` with deletion标记\n70: - [ ] **7.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go` — implement `cleanupPVCs(namespace, ownerRef)` respecting ReclaimPolicy\n71: - [ ] **7.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go` — implement `cleanupOrphanedResources(sandbox)` for AR-006-061\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## Phase 8: Lifecycle Events & Webhooks\n76: \n77: - [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/events.go` — implement `emitDeletionEvent(sandbox, reason)` using k8s event recorder\n78: - [ ] **8.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/events.go` — implement `sendDeletionWebhook(sandbox, config)` with retry (max 3)\n79: - [ ] **8.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/events.go` — implement `logDeletionAudit(entry)` for audit trail\n80: - [ ] **8.4** Integrate events into DeleteSandbox flow\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Phase 9: Error Handling & Retry\n85: \n86: - [ ] **9.1** Map new error types to HTTP status codes in `server.go` handleError method\n87: - [ ] **9.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/retry.go` — implement `retryDeletion(ctx, fn, maxRetries)` with exponential backoff\n88: - [ ] **9.3** Add retry logic to garbage collector for transient deletion failures\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## Phase 10: Integration with AR-005\n93: \n94: - [ ] **10.1** Hook into sandbox creation failure path — call cleanup on rollback\n95: - [ ] **10.2** Use existing k8s_client from AR-005 for all deletion operations\n96: - [ ] **10.3** Integrate with informer watches for sandbox state tracking\n97: - [ ] **10.4** Reuse store's DeleteSandbox/GetSandbox methods\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## Phase 11: Unit Tests\n102: \n103: - [ ] **11.1** `pkg/workloadmanager/delete_test.go` — TestDeleteSandbox_Success (AR-006-001)\n104: - [ ] **11.2** `pkg/workloadmanager/delete_test.go` — TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound (AR-006-004)\n105: - [ ] **11.3** `pkg/workloadmanager/delete_test.go` — TestDeleteSandbox_ForceDelete (AR-006-003)\n106: - [ ] **11.4** `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_test.go` — TestDrainConnections (AR-006-012)\n107: - [ ] **11.5** `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_test.go` — TestExecutePreDeleteHook (AR-006-011)\n108: - [ ] **11.6** `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go` — TestIsExpired_TTL (AR-006-020)\n109: - [ ] **11.7** `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go` — TestIsExpired_IdleTimeout (AR-006-021)\n110: - [ ] **11.8** `pkg/workloadmanager/batch_test.go` — TestDeleteAllInNamespace (AR-006-030)\n111: - [ ] **11.9** `pkg/workloadmanager/batch_test.go` — TestDeleteByLabelSelector (AR-006-031)\n112: - [ ] **11.10** `pkg/workloadmanager/events_test.go` — TestEmitDeletionEvent (AR-006-040)\n113: - [ ] **11.11** `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup_test.go` — TestCleanupServices (AR-006-050)\n114: - [ ] **11.12** `pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup_test.go` — TestCleanupPVCs_RetainPolicy (AR-006-052)\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## Phase 12: Integration Tests\n119: \n120: - [ ] **12.1** `pkg/workloadmanager/e2e_delete_test.go` — E2E sandbox deletion flow\n121: - [ ] **12.2** E2E graceful shutdown with active connections\n122: - [ ] **12.3** E2E TTL expiration and auto-cleanup\n123: - [ ] **12.4** E2E batch deletion with 100+ sandboxes\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## Phase 13: Verification\n128: \n129: - [ ] **13.1** `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` — successful compilation\n130: - [ ] **13.2** `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` — all uni